          boolean reportResults
          Indication for whether the receiver will report the result.

        • timeoutInMilliseconds

          int timeoutInMilliseconds
          If timeout (milliseconds) is set (>0) then this run is aborted when it takes more time to complete. The actual time to complete (again in milliseconds) is reported

        • severity

          Severity severity
          Used to indicate whether a task has critical or warning severity when a check fails. By default, severity is set to critical.
